theorem Topology.interior_closure_iUnion_eq_interior_iUnion_closure
    {X ι : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] (A : ι → Set X) :
    interior (closure (⋃ i, A i : Set X)) =
      interior (⋃ i, closure (A i) : Set X) := by
  -- `closure` distributes over (indexed) unions.
  have h : closure (⋃ i, (A i : Set X)) = ⋃ i, closure (A i : Set X) := by
    simpa using closure_iUnion
  simpa [h]

theorem Topology.interior_closure_empty {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] :
    interior (closure (∅ : Set X)) = (∅ : Set X) := by
  simpa [closure_empty, interior_empty]
